request.description:
üéØ **NEW API - Generate QR Code for AutoPay Subscription**

This API creates a subscription and returns QR code data that React developers can use to display a scannable QR code.

**Request Body:**
- `user_id` (required): User identifier
- `plan_id` (required): Subscription plan ID
- `amount` (required): Amount in rupees (minimum 1)
- `upi` (optional): User's UPI ID
- `target_app` (optional): Target UPI app (default: com.phonepe.app)

**Response:**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "QR Code generated successfully",
  "data": {
    "merchant_order_id": "MO_...",
    "merchant_subscription_id": "MS_...",
    "phonepe_order_id": "...",
    "state": "PENDING",
    "expire_at": "2026-02-21T12:00:00Z",
    "qr_code": {
      "base64": "data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANS...",
      "intent_url": "upi://pay?...",
      "decoded_params": {
        "pa": "merchant@upi",
        "pn": "Merchant Name",
        "am": "1.00",
        "cu": "INR",
        "tn": "Transaction note"
      }
    },
    "instructions": {
      "step_1": "Open any UPI app (PhonePe, GPay, Paytm, etc.)",
      "step_2": "Tap on 'Scan QR Code' option",
      "step_3": "Scan this QR code with your phone camera",
      "step_4": "Verify amount and complete payment"
    }
  }
}
```

**How to Use in React:**

```jsx
// 1. Call the API
const response = await fetch('{{base_url}}/api/phonepe/autopay/generate-qr', {
  method: 'POST',
  headers: {
    'Content-Type': 'application/json',
    'Accept': 'application/json'
  },
  body: JSON.stringify({
    user_id: 'user123',
    plan_id: 'monthly_plan',
    amount: 99,
    upi: 'user@okaxis'
  })
});

const data = await response.json();

// 2. Display QR Code
<img 
  src={data.data.qr_code.base64} 
  alt="Scan to Pay" 
  style={{ width: '300px', height: '300px' }}
/>

// 3. Show Instructions
<div>
  <h3>Scan QR Code to Pay</h3>
  <p>{data.data.instructions.step_1}</p>
  <p>{data.data.instructions.step_2}</p>
  <p>{data.data.instructions.step_3}</p>
  <p>{data.data.instructions.step_4}</p>
</div>

// 4. Save subscription ID for status check
const subscriptionId = data.data.merchant_subscription_id;
```

**Features:**
- ‚úÖ Returns base64 encoded QR code image
- ‚úÖ Ready to use in <img> tag
- ‚úÖ No external QR library needed in frontend
- ‚úÖ Includes UPI intent URL for deep linking
- ‚úÖ Decoded parameters for custom UI
- ‚úÖ Step-by-step instructions for users

**‚ö†Ô∏è NO CSRF TOKEN NEEDED - This is an API route!**
